# Base URL of the FastAPI backend (uv run uvicorn backend.api.app:app --reload).
# The browser calls this directly (decision 0008, clarification 6) — no Next.js
# proxy route exists, so this must be reachable from the browser, not just the
# Next.js server process. Read in exactly one place (src/lib/api/http.ts's
# apiBaseUrl()) — never hardcoded elsewhere; missing this throws a
# CLIENT_CONFIGURATION_ERROR instead of a raw exception.
#
# Local development:
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000
#
# Future public deployment (illustrative only — no hosting is provisioned yet,
# see HANDOFF.md's "Portfolio Roadmap"): set this to the real backend URL,
# e.g. NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend-host.example
